    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-12-29T17:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-12-29T17:36:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <head>475. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d475fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 27 VIET S. Top Secret; Immediate;
                        Exdis; Ivory. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BWP1">William
                            Bundy</persName>, cleared with <persName corresp="#p_SB1">Bromley
                            Smith</persName>, and initialed by <persName corresp="#p_BGW1"
                            >Ball</persName>. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>, the
                        Department of Defense, the White House, CINCPAC, Bangkok, and
                        Vientiane.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1964-12-29T17:36:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1964—5:36 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1365. Highest levels today<note n="2" xml:id="d475fn2">Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName> left Washington at 9 a.m. for the Texas
                        White House to discuss Vietnam and other topics with the President and
                            <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">McGeorge Bundy</persName>. (Johnson Library,
                        Rusk Appointment Book) No record of the meeting has been found.</note>
                    reached negative decision on proposal your 1975<note n="3" xml:id="d475fn3">
                        <ref target="#d472">Document 472</ref>.</note> for reprisal action for BOQ
                    bombing. We will be <pb facs="1081" n="1053" xml:id="pg_1053"/> sending fuller
                    statement of reasoning and considerations affecting future actions, after
                    Secretary’s return from Texas tonight.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
